NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|At trick two, Eddy was returning a spade for me to ruff, since he knows both declarer and I are out. The problem is, he needs to give me a suit preference in spades, so I know what to return. By leading a low spade, he is telling me to return a club, the lower of the remaining non-trump suits. Had he returned a high spade, say the 9, that would have said he wants a diamond back, the higher of the remaining non-trump suits. Since he has no preference, he should return a middle spade, say the 6. That says, "partner you choose."  |
PG| ***** 15 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Once I ruff and return a club, declarer should be reasonably confident of making at least 4. The clubs are all good, and there are no diamond losers. So, declarer should draw 2 rounds of hearts, if the Queen does not come down then he loses the heart, otherwise he will make 5. On this hand, he should make 5. No big deal in IMPs, but important in Match Points.|
