cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|No Ed, your bid was okay. Your partner's was not. Basically, once partner preempts, use the law of total tricks to determine how high to go, assuming you are not strong enough to bid game. So, with only an 8 card fit, a 3 level bid is not safe.  West should pass. The 3S bid did give Eddy a problem, but this is one of those hands where "the operation was a success, but the patient died ", :).|
