NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|By that I mean, the 3S bid gave Eddy a problem, and he chose an action that would have worked out badly. Normally, East should pass. In general, once the preempter opens, he is out of the auction unless partner asks him a question. A simple raise is not a question--only 2N or a new suit are questions. However, there are occasional exceptions. |
