mb|1C|mb|1H|mb|2D|mb|p|mb|2S|mb|p|mb|3H|NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|When there are 2 suits remaining in which stoppers are unknown, a bid of one of those suits shows a stopper. For example, had Ginny bid 3C rather than 2S, then there are 2 remaining unbid suits in terms of stoppers, spades and hearts. In that case (not this hand), my 3H bid would show a heart stopper and deny a spade stopper. However, on this hand, we have bid 3 suits therefore, if I had a stopper in hearts, I can bid 3N. By bidding 3H, I am denying a heart stopper and asking Ginny to bid 3N with hearts stopped. So, my 3H cue bid would have a different meaning depending on whether or not Ginny had bid spades.|
